ibmHprRtGlobeConnTrigger.name: ibmHprRtGlobeConnTrigger
ibmHprRtGlobeConnTrigger.description: This object is used to trigger an HPR route test of the physical path of an existing RTP Connection. The format of this object is: nceid-length.nceid.tcid, where - nceid-length: 1 octet. valid values are 1-8. - nceid: 1-8 octets. - tcid: 8 octets.

ibmHprRtGlobeNameTrigger.name: ibmHprRtGlobeNameTrigger
ibmHprRtGlobeNameTrigger.description: This object is used to trigger an HPR route test of the physical path of an existing or non-existing RTP Connection. The names will be used to generate a HPR Route which may or may not match an existing RTP Connection; but must be reside on a current or potential RTP Connection endpoint node. The format of this object is: netid.lu-name.mode-name, where - netid: 1-8 octets. - period: 1 octet. - lu-name: 1-8 octets. - period: 1 octet. - mode-name: 1-8 octets.

ibmHprRtGenTable.name: ibmHprRtGenTable
ibmHprRtGenTable.description: The HPR Route Test General Results Table.

ibmHprRtGenEntry.name: ibmHprRtGenEntry
ibmHprRtGenEntry.description: The HPR Route Test Id is used to index to this table. This Id is an integer that begins at 1 and is incremented with each route test executed on the agent node.

ibmHprRtGenTestId.name: ibmHprRtGenTestId
ibmHprRtGenTestId.description: The route test id. This Id is an integer that begins at 1 and is incremented with each route test execution.

ibmHprRtGenTestType.name: ibmHprRtGenTestType
ibmHprRtGenTestType.description: The route test type. This indicates whether the route test was triggered by setting the: 1. global connection trigger, or 2. global name trigger.

ibmHprRtGenConnTrigger.name: ibmHprRtGenConnTrigger
ibmHprRtGenConnTrigger.description: This object will be valid if the route test was triggered by setting the global connection trigger. If the route test was triggered by setting the global name trigger, this object will return the zero-length string. When it is not null, the format of this object is: nceid-length.nceid.tcid, where - nceid-length: 1 octet. valid values are 1-8. - nceid: 1-8 octets. - tcid: 8 octets.

ibmHprRtGenNameTrigger.name: ibmHprRtGenNameTrigger
ibmHprRtGenNameTrigger.description: This object will be valid if the route test was triggered by setting the global name trigger. If the route test was triggered by setting the global connection trigger, this object will return the zero-length string. When it is not null, the format of this object is: netid.lu-name.mode-name, where - netid: 1-8 octets. - period: 1 octet. - lu-name: 1-8 octets. - period: 1 octet. - mode-name: 1-8 octets.

ibmHprRtGenResult.name: ibmHprRtGenResult
ibmHprRtGenResult.description: The route test result. This indicates whether the route test was: 1. successfully executed, or 2. in progress and has not completed yet, or 3. no response was received from one or more nodes, or 4. the nce id used to trigger the route test was invalid, or 5. the tcid used to trigger the route test was invalid, or 6. the lu name used to trigger the route test was invalid, or 7. the mode name used to trigger the route test was invalid for the lu name specified, or 8. a contiguous hpr route from this node to the target lu does not exist and cannot be created.

ibmHprRtGenSenseCode.name: ibmHprRtGenSenseCode
ibmHprRtGenSenseCode.description: The SNA sense data that corresponds to the route test result.

ibmHprRtGenCosName.name: ibmHprRtGenCosName
ibmHprRtGenCosName.description: The class of service name used for this route test.

ibmHprRtGenRscv.name: ibmHprRtGenRscv
ibmHprRtGenRscv.description: The route selection control vector used for this route test.

ibmHprRtDetTable.name: ibmHprRtDetTable
ibmHprRtDetTable.description: The HPR Route Test Detailed Results Table.

ibmHprRtDetEntry.name: ibmHprRtDetEntry
ibmHprRtDetEntry.description: The HPR Route Test Id and HPR Route Sub Test Id are used to index this table. The Test Id is an integer that begins at 1 and is incremented with each route test execution. The Sub Test Id is an integer that begins at 1 and is incremented with each node along the path being tested.

ibmHprRtDetTestId.name: ibmHprRtDetTestId
ibmHprRtDetTestId.description: The route test id. This Id is an integer that begins at 1 and is incremented with each route test execution. If this object has the same value as the ibmHprRtGenTestId, then the two objects apply to the same route test.

ibmHprRtDetSubTestId.name: ibmHprRtDetSubTestId
ibmHprRtDetSubTestId.description: The sub test id. This Id is an integer that begins at 1 and is incremented with each node along the path being tested. The last entry of the test will be designated by a value 255.

ibmHprRtDetDestNode.name: ibmHprRtDetDestNode
ibmHprRtDetDestNode.description: The destination node name for this portion of the route test.

ibmHprRtDetPriorNode.name: ibmHprRtDetPriorNode
ibmHprRtDetPriorNode.description: The name of the node which is prior to the destination node for this portion of the route test.

ibmHprRtDetLastTgNumber.name: ibmHprRtDetLastTgNumber
ibmHprRtDetLastTgNumber.description: The last TG number for this portion of the route test.

ibmHprRtDetRtripTime.name: ibmHprRtDetRtripTime
ibmHprRtDetRtripTime.description: The round trip time for this portion of the route test. It is the total time from when the test frame was sent by this node to the time when the test frame was received back at this node.

ibmHprRtDetResult.name: ibmHprRtDetResult
ibmHprRtDetResult.description: The result of this portion of the route test. It indicates whether this portion of the route test was: 1. successfully executed, or 2. no response was received.
